<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="42" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dayton</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 472.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-08"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 8, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my Nos. 461 and 465,
                            respecting the imprisonment of Mr. J. H. Mansfield, the United States
                            consul at Tabasco, I transmit herewith a copy of a letter of the 6th of
                            November last, addressed by Charles Jones, esq., to Mr. Adams, our
                            minister at London, upon the subject, I will thank you to ask for the
                            release of Mr. Mansfield, that he may be permitted to proceed to the
                            United States, and you will also request explanations of the proceedings
                            against him.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">William L. Dayton</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>